      "message": "\u003e Allow me to discuss here:\n\u003e Now we have two pools with wificell fixtures: wificell and wificell-pre-cq (now renames as wificell-cq). Is it better we create another group, say group:wificell_cq? \n\nWhy? The existing group is just to differentiate from \u0027mainline\u0027, with sub-attributes to reflect each role (so, \u0027wificell_cq\u0027 would be the role-specific sub-attribute).\n\n\u003e If so, is it a good idea to have \"wificell_cq_informational\" sub-attribute for those CQ tests that are not stable enough to reject offending CLs?\n\nIsn\u0027t that exactly what \u0027wificell_unstable\u0027 is about?",
